Rating: 3
This recipe packs an awful lot of flavour for the time involved. It's quick, easy and can be made at the last minute. I halved the serving portions by directly halving the primary ingredients in the recipe - beans, tomatoes and water, but only cut back spices 0%-25% and reduced oil. Used 1 TBSP oil for 3 onions in a non-stick pan, 3 TBSP whole cumin seeds ground, 3 TBSP dried greek oregano in bunches ground, 4TSBP chile powder and 4 TBSP Columbian ground medium roast coffee (had it on hand and tried 5 stores on phone for instant expresso and couldn't find it). Used 1/2 tsp Chipotle Pepper (stock regularly) & extra garlic. It was quick and delicious. Served on basmati rice, with non-fat sour cream, cocoa powder and green onions. It was spicy but not too spicy and had great depth of flavour. Retains flavour well as reheated 2 days later in microwave and served with sweet potato. My partner thought it was yummy. My friend found it tasty for lunch. Simple and little effort. Tastes like you fussed a lot more. The dark colour is exotic. I think it's quite a forgiving recipe which can be tweeked to your liking. I wouldn't omit the coffee (instant expresso or roasted instant coffee) or chipotle pepper if you want the depth. And I agree with another reviewer, if possible don't use chipotle in adobe sauce. The plain chipotle pepper powder would be preferrable and more discreet. The abobe sauce would likely add more fiery heat than a subtle smoked flavour. Will definitely make again. Enjoy!!!

