Well, I thought I had a previous message but it didn't get sent. So I'll try again. When you need chipotle chili powder for this recipe, order it from Tierra Vegetables (web site is at http://www.tierravegetables.com). You won't find the chili powder listed. You'll have to email them to get the exact price and shipping but I am sure it was $20 plus S&H for 1/4 ounce. I use it in everything...guacamole, chili, eggs, burritos, etc I has incredible depth. Don't be lured by cheap imitations....they are worthless. This stuff is priceless and to be savored and enjoyed. Just the smell will convince you. I have no financial interest in them but wish I did. They are located in Healdsburg CA.

