Rating: 3
Very good. I used a bag of fresh beans because it's what I had on-hand. Also, I cannot find instant espresso in this town, so I brewed some really strong coffee and used a cup of that. I cooked my black beans in chicken broth and used the remaining liquid as a substitute for the other cup of water. Added cayenne pepper at the end because I didn't have chipotle powder. Still it was extremely good and probably really close to the original recipe. The honey adds a nice sweetness that I thought I wouldn't like, but suprisingly did! Make it, you'll like it!

