A great veggie chili recipe. I used 5 cans of black beans and a bag of veggie crumbles. I also added 1/4 cup of chocolate chips, which gave it a great, subtle flavor.

Rating: 4
Just made this for a Superbowl party. Truly delicious. I was looking for a "traditional with a twist" chili recipe, and I've found my new standard. It's not very spicy, so if you like it hot you'll need more spice. I added the chocolate directly to the chili instead of leaving it out as a garnish (was worried my guests would get squeemish and not try it). It added such an incredible depth of flavor. I served it with only sour cream and corn chips, and it went FAST.

